    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:16pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Rizal’s Final Moments: Bravery and Dignity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="europe2">
    <property name="enabled">
     <bool>false</bool>
    </property>
    <property name="geometry">
     <rect>
      <x>570</x>
      <y>200</y>
      <width>411</width>
      <height>491</height>
     </rect>
    </property>
    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">

    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }

</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;On &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;December 30, 1896&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Bagumbayan Field&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; (now &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Rizal Park&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Manila&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;), José Rizal faced the firing squad. He was 35 years old. Despite the unjust charges and his imminent death, Rizal faced his execution with remarkable                   and            . In his final moments, he refused to show fear or hatred toward his captors or the colonial authorities. Instead, he remained calm, dignified, and resolute in his commitment to his country.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Before his execution, Rizal wrote a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;farewell poem,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; font-style:italic; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Mi Último Adiós&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;My Last Farewell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;), which became one of his most cherished works. In the poem, he expressed his deep love for the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Philippine islands&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, his longing for their freedom, and his hopes that his death would inspire future generations to continue the fight for independence. Rizal’s words conveyed both a sense of peace and a deep sense of hope for the Filipino people. He declared that his sacrifice was made in the name &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;of                , and he encouraged his fellow countrymen to rise up and fight for a free and just nation. Rizal's final stanza reads:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
